Package: usagebar
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Tyler Casey <tc@tylerbuilds.com>
Description: Premium AI usage tracker for Linux
 UsageBar is a native GTK3 system tray application that provides
 real-time visibility into your AI provider limits. Inspired by 
 CodexBar.app for macOS, UsageBar brings a rich, expandable UI to 
 Ubuntu and other Linux distributions.
 .
 Features:
  - Multi-provider support (Claude, OpenAI, Gemini, Cursor, Factory)
  - Color-coded progress bars with emoji indicators
  - Historical usage tracking with sparkline visualizations
  - Usage trend analysis (24h charts)
  - Dark/light theme auto-detection
  - Rich tooltips and status indicators
  - Dashboard shortcuts for quick access
 .
 UsageBar helps you never hit a "limit reached" surprise again
 by providing at-a-glance status for all your AI providers.
Depends: python3 (>= 3.8), python3-gi, gir1.2-appindicator3-0.1, libsqlite3-0
Priority: optional
Section: utils
